race.comment: Tricky race. LA ROUX (10) resumes having shown plenty of ability as a 2yo, winning two on the bounce dominantly before placing to Steel Trap in a handy race. Forgiving the flop in Listed company before a spell when coming to the end of her campaign, and she's trialled well leading in. GIN SPIRIT (7) did beat LA ROUX in said Listed race in Adelaide but didn't come up in two runs last campaign. She's certainly good enough and can do better this time in. INNOCENT ENUFF (1) mixes her form but can cross these and take catching. OCTRAIN (5) has struggled to threaten of late but should find this a little easier and gets some weight relief with the 4kg claimer engaged. Worth keeping safe in minors.
